<h1>Remake &ndash; GNU Make with comprehensible tracing and a debugger</h1>
<P>

<P><tt>remake</tt> is a patched and modernized version of GNU make
utility that adds improved error reporting, the ability to trace
execution in a comprehensible way, and a debugger. 

<p>However, if you are looking for the plain vanilla GNU Make, try <a
href="http://www.gnu.org/software/make/">here.</a>
We also have a couple of cool debuggers for 
<a href="http://bashdb.sourceforge.net">GNU Bash</a> and 
<a href="http://bashdb.sourceforge.net/pydb">Python</a>.

<div style="clear: left;">&nbsp;</div>
<ul>
  <li><a HREF="http://bashdb.sourceforge.net/remake/make.html">
    GNU Make Documentation online</a>
  </li>
</ul>

